track_notes:
Track for Haglebu parking -> LA/BU-060 -> LA/BU-136 -> LA/BU-156 -> Haglebu parking.

Path to LA/BU-136 and later to LA/BU-156 is non optimal and in some places very steep and rather dangerous, so do not follow it blindly!
track_title: GPX for tripple activation, where LA/BU-136 is the second summit

track_notes:
Winter 2024, lots of snow and extrem difficult from bottom to topp, I used snowshoes and my snow/ice climbing gear. Not possible to climb this summit with only simple foot gear in rough winter, winter 2024 was extrem lots of snow and ice. If you decide to make this winter trip you will need Mountaineering gear or at least Crampons and an ice axe and good boots.

Summer trip is for the lazy :) no just kidding, I will be doing this track with my wife this summer 2024 :)

---

I like to Check-inn as close as possible from the summit, and within the 25m zone as stated in the SOTA rules.
(Typically the contour line is 25 metres below peak height of the summit).

I use SOTA Goat Summit Tracker with GPS tracking, most of the times, depending of battery status on the phone, as I run 3 or 4 apps and taking pictures, so on longer tracks I may reduce the apps or photos, or take my Cannon cam along. Specially on winter time when is down to -10/-25 degrees :)
